In [ ]:
# ref: https://chatbotslife.com/cnn-image-classification-using-cifar-10-dataset-on-google-colab-tpu-750da8cd8510

#normalizing the inputs to 0.0 - 1.0 from 0 to 255
xtrain = xtrain.astype('float32')
xtest = xtest.astype('float32')

xtrain = xtrain/255.0
xtest = xtest/255.0

#Center around 0 (-1,1)
xtrain = (xtrain-0.5)/0.5
xtest = (xtest -0.5)/0.5

Model Definition

In [ ]:
initializer = tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal()
model1 = Sequential()
model1.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),input_shape=xtrain.shape[1:],strides=1))
model1.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
model1.add(Activation('relu'))
model1.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),strides=1))
model1.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
model1.add(Activation('relu'))
model1.add(Flatten())
model1.add(Dense(20,kernel_initializer=initializer))
model1.add(Activation('relu'))
model1.add(Dense(10,kernel_initializer=initializer))
model1.add(Activation('softmax'))

    plt.imshow(xtrain_aug3[i], cmap=plt.cm.binary)
    plt.xlabel(label_names[ytrain[i][0]])
plt.show()

initializer = tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal()

model2.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),input_shape=xtrain.shape[1:],strides=1))
model2.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
model2.add(Activation('relu'))
model2.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),strides=1))
model2.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
model2.add(Activation('relu'))
model2.add(Flatten())
model2.add(Dense(20,kernel_initializer=initializer))
model2.add(Activation('relu'))
model2.add(Dense(10,kernel_initializer=initializer))
model2.add(Activation('softmax'))

# ref: https://chatbotslife.com/cnn-image-classification-using-cifar-10-dataset-on-google-colab-tpu-750da8cd8510

xtest = xtest.astype('float32')

xtrain = xtrain/255.0
xtest = xtest/255.0

#Center around 0 (-1,1)
xtrain = (xtrain-0.5)/0.5
xtest = (xtest -0.5)/0.5

Model Defination for Unlabelled Data

In [20]:
initializer = tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal()
model3 = Sequential()
model3.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),input_shape=xtrain.shape[1:],strides=1))
model3.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
model3.add(Activation('relu'))
model3.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),strides=1))
model3.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
model3.add(Activation('relu'))
model3.add(Flatten())
model3.add(Dense(20,kernel_initializer=initializer))
model3.add(Activation('relu'))
model3.add(Dense(3,kernel_initializer=initializer))
model3.add(Activation('softmax'))

Baseline Model

In [25]:
initializer = tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal()
baseline = tf.keras.Sequential()
baseline.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),input_shape=xtrain.shape[1:],strides=1,activation='relu'))
baseline.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
baseline.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),strides=1,activation='relu'))
baseline.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
baseline.add(Flatten())
baseline.add(Dense(20,kernel_initializer=initializer,activation='relu'))
baseline.add(Dense(10,kernel_initializer=initializer,activation='softmax'))
In [26]:
# sparse categorical loss is without the one hot encoded target
optimize_adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam()
baseline.compile(optimizer=optimize_adam,loss=tf.keras.losses.sparse_categorical_crossentropy,metrics=['sparse_categorical_accuracy'])
In [27]:
baseline_fit = baseline.fit(xtrain_aside,ytrain_aside,epochs=1000,validation_data=(xtest,ytest))

Transfer Learning

In [29]:
initializer = tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal()
transfer_model = Sequential()
transfer_model.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),input_shape=xtrain.shape[1:],strides=1,activation='relu'))
transfer_model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
transfer_model.add(Conv2D(filters=10,kernel_size=(5,5),strides=1,activation='relu'))
transfer_model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=2))
transfer_model.add(Flatten())
transfer_model.add(Dense(20,kernel_initializer=initializer,activation='relu'))

IBM Calculation

In [8]:
def ibm_conversion(clean_signal,noise_signal):
  ibm = np.zeros((clean_signal.shape))
  ibm[clean_signal > noise_signal] = 1
  return ibm
In [9]:
train_ibm_label = []
for j in range(1200):
  ibm = ibm_conversion(train_clean[j], train_noise[j])
  train_ibm_label.append(ibm)

In [13]:
gru_model = tf.keras.Sequential();
gru_model.add(layers.GRU(513, return_sequences=True))
gru_model.add(layers.Dropout(rate = 0.2))

gru_model.add(layers.Dropout(rate = 0.2))
gru_model.add(layers.Dense(513, activation='sigmoid',kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal()))

In [30]:
def SNR_func(y,ypred):
  num = np.sum(np.square(y))
  dem = np.sum(np.square(y-ypred))
  return 10 * np.log10(num/dem)

Calculating all the SNR values

In [31]:
mean_snr = 0
for i in range(1200):
    print(i)
    s, sr = librosa.load(val_loc+val_lis[i], sr=None)
    Si = librosa.stft(s, n_fft=1024, hop_length=512)
    clean = librosa.istft(val_clean[i],hop_length=512)
    Shat = SRecon[i]
    Shat = Shat[:Si.shape[1]]
    recon = librosa.istft(Shat.T,hop_length=512)
    new_snr = SNR_func(clean, recon)
    print(new_snr)
    mean_snr += new_snr
    
mean_snr /= 1200

In [34]:
test_noisy = []
test_noisy_ab=[]
for i in range(len(test_lis)):
    s, sr = librosa.load(test_loc+test_lis[i], sr=None)
    Si = librosa.stft(s, n_fft=1024, hop_length=512)
    #r = math.ceil(Si.shape[1]/10)*10
    padding = np.ones((513,195))*(0.000001+0.000001j)
    padding[:, :Si.shape[1]] = Si
    #padding = padding.reshape((int(r/10),10,513))
    test_noisy.append(padding.T)
    test_noisy_ab.append(np.abs(padding.T))

import soundfile as sf
final_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/Deep_Learning/te-clean/'
for i in range(400):
    s, sr = librosa.load(test_loc+test_lis[i], sr=None)
    recon = librosa.istft(SRecon[i].T, hop_length=512)
    recon = recon[:len(s)]
